column5: What are your best fish of 2012? There's still lots of time to upgrade but I think we all need to get back to fishing before winternet takes hold.  Here are mine (I know a lot of them aren't very big)  Brown-23" Rainbow-17" Brookie-9" Salmon-36" Pike-25" Chain pickeral-10" (first) Walleye-6" (first) Striped bass-20" Smallmouth-18" Largemouth-19" Bonefish-20" Snapper-12" Bluerunner-9" Perch-12" Crappie-9" Flounder15" Carp-28" Bullhead-17" Channel cat-25"

Pike- around 40" Walleye-around 25 Perch-around 14 Bass - Around 20 Smelt-around 10 Brookie-around 15 Rainbow-around 20 Laker- around 20 Ling - not sure but must be around 32-35 white bass- 16 sucker- around 18-20 EDIT: Splake - 18  I don't measure most of my fish as you can tell....not easy to do from a canoe  You got lots of species on your list! Well done!
Haha, you too. Most of mine were guesses too.

Speckle trout - 13 1/4" Speckle trout - 12" Speckle trout - 11" Speckle trout - 10" Speckle trout - 09" Speckle trout - 8 1/2"   That's all I've been targeting this past couple of years  You did good Christopher
Largemouth Bass - 18" Smallmouth Bass - 14" White sucker - 23" Pike - 21" Walleye - 18" Crappie - 11" Perch - 15" Bullhead - 15" Brook Trout - 8"
I only got one PB this year but it was the one that I've been chasing all my life.    23 inch, 6 pound brook trout.
Brook trout. 24.5in, 6.89lbs.    I think that's about it for PB's this year.
Nice guys! I just meant the best of this year though.

Longnose Gar: 38" Largemouth Bass: 20.5"/5.3lbs Smallmouth Bass: 15" Rock Bass: 7.5" Pumpkinseed: 6" Bluegill: 8.5" Black Crappie: 11" Yellow Perch: 10.5" Walleye: 16.5" Northern Pike: 29.5" Muskellunge: 27" Common Carp: approx. 22lbs Brown Trout: 9" Rainbow Trout: 16" Lake Trout: 20" Splake: 10" Of those, 3 are new species I've caught (Bluegill, Lake Trout and Splake)

My fishing efforts are focused almost entirely on spring and fall steelhead lately, because that's when I have the time to get out. After banking a 37.5" fish two years ago I haven't come close to a PB in a while.  A couple fish in the low 30's, and one lost fish that would have been a close call PB but nothing on the bank.

These are my biggest, although I am still hoping to catch a larger walleye before the end of the year.   29 3/4" walleye   30" Laker   My wife's monster laker, not sure of length but close to 34" I think   38" Musky
Can I dream a PB Speckle like those in the pictures? I keep telling myself

i usually don't have a scale or tape with me while fishing, so you'll have to settle for pics of my 2012 PB's.  4ft or so...    i believe my biggest couple perch of the year are in there somewhere...    mrs kitty...    biggest was 28"...
This is one of 2 32.5" walleyes i got this year.......my PB this year and ever.

Largemouth bass: 19.5" Smallmouth bass: 17" pike: 31" walleye: 16.5" rainbow trout: 15" brown trout: 23" brook trout: 12" chinook salmon: 36-38" yellow perch: 12.5" black crappie: 14.5" (monster) bluegill: 9-10" mirror carp: 24" dog fish: 29"  species I have not caught this year (or ever): musky, lake trout
